SIMPLE: unbending
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unbending
<hw>Un*bend"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[In senses 1, 2, and 3, pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>bending</ets>; in sense 4, properly p. pr. of
<ets>unbend</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not bending; not suffering
flexure; not yielding to pressure; stiff; -- applied to material
things.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Flies o'er the <qex>unbending</qex> corn, and skims along the
main.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unyielding in will; not subject to persuasion or
influence; inflexible; resolute; -- applied to persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Unyielding in nature; unchangeable; fixed; --
applied to abstract ideas; <as>as, <ex>unbending</ex>
truths</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Devoted to relaxation or amusement.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It may entertain your lordships at an <qex>unbending</qex>
hour.</q> <rj><qau>Rowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*bend"ing*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*bend"ing*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbenevolence</ent>⟦br⟧
